>> title: Lemon Chicken and Orzo Soup
>> servings: 4
>> source: https://www.americastestkitchen.com/recipes/10357-lemon-chicken-and-orzo-soup

1. Melt @unsalted butter{2%tbsp} in large saucepan over medium heat. Add @onion{1%small} and cook until softened, about 4 minutes. Increase heat to medium-high; add @chicken broth{8%cups}, @sprigs thyme{2} sprigs, 1 teaspoon salt, and Â½ teaspoon @Salt and pepper{}; and bring to boil. Add @orzo{1%cup} and cook until tender, 12 to 14 minutes. Remove from heat and discard thyme sprigs.

2. Whisk @egg yolks{6%large} and @lemon juice{6%tbsp} in bowl until combined. Whisking constantly, slowly pour yolk mixture into hot soup. Stir in @rotisserie chicken{2%cups}, cover, and let sit for 10 minutes, until soup is thickened and chicken is warmed through. Sprinkle with @chives{2%tbsp}. Serve.
